\begin_inset Formula $x_{(0)}$
\end_inset

 again.
 We use the convention that 
\begin_inset Formula $u$
\end_inset

 varies between 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon$
\end_inset

.
 This is to ensure that 
\begin_inset Formula $dx^{i}/du\sim1$
\end_inset

 that is we can't assume it to be arbitrarily small.
 If we had taken 
\begin_inset Formula $u$
\end_inset

 to range from 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

 then 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta x/\delta u\sim\mathcal{O}(\epsilon)$
\end_inset

 as illustrated in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
