With these ingredients in place we are now ready to give the complete proof
 of the proposition.
 The basic idea, as the astute reader would have already guessed, is to
 break a finite loop into arbitrarily small loops using the observation
 made above.
 Then we apply the result which was valid for small loops and put the pieces
 together with the hope of being able to, and indeed we do, establish the
 result in general.
\end_layout

